data.description: Delightful Colonial home set on a 1.65 acre wooded parcel. Enjoy the tranquility of this peaceful countryside area of Dover while having quick access to shopping, major routes, and the seacoast. Take in the quaint setting as you make your way up the paver path adorned with fruit trees, annuals, perennials and mature landscaping. This interior is packed with updates and sure to please. The kitchen features stainless appliances, stainless farmers sink w/pull out faucet, new hardware, LED lighting, and a cozy soapstone stove. Both bathrooms have been tastefully re-fashioned with new vanities, toilets, faucets, led lighting and new flooring. The main part of the home offers space for a formal dining, living area, and separate  office spaces well suited for work from home professionals. This unique layout also offers two first floor bedrooms. Check out the recently added addition boasting an open concept entertaining area with cathedral ceilings, natural stone hearth, milled red oak flooring and high efficiency wood stove. Just off the back of the home there is a large deck with views over the wooded acreage. Upstairs there is a primary suite big enough to host a party with new berber carpets, walk-in closet, organizers, and an en-suite bath. The major systems have been revamped over the past few years offering newer water heater, water filtration as well as newer propane furnace with central ac.
